{
  "texts": [
    "But it was society that gave a practical shape to his dreams of learning a language.",
    "Pride (1979) argued that three variables were essential for good learning: opportunity, motivation, and aptitude.",
    "Learner's exposure to language-speaking environments and situations wherein making use of English and practicing was required was mandatory for effective language learning.",
    "The function of the teacher is extremely important in the classroom setting, but it is especially important in language classes.",
    "They are the source of inspiration and motivation for their students."
  ]
}